The man will appear in court on Thursday for murder after the boy died in hospital, while a second child survived the attack. JOHANNESBURG A man faces a charge of murder after he allegedly stabbed a policeman's son. The incident occurred in Kwanonqaba earlier this week. The 12-year-old died in hospital, while a second child survived the attack. The police's Malcolm Poje says: He has been charged for murder and he is due to appear in court tomorrow. 